ctised%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAhar%20Pynes%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-280153%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ahars%20are%20used%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-280153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAhars%20are%20used%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months.%20Picture%20Credits%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiawaterportal.org%2Farticles%2Fahar-pynes-traditional-flood-water-harvesting-systems-can-help-revive-agriculture-south%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20Water%20Portal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrevalent%20in%20South%20Bihar%2C%20Ahar%20Pynes%20are%20traditional%20floodwater%20harvesting%20systems%20that%20work%20as%20reservoirs%20to%20cut%20the%20flow%20of%20water%20and%20store%20it%20for%20irrigation%20and%20other%20purposes.%20These%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F447032%2Fshyam-sunder-jyani-teacher-turned-environmentalist-restored-mining-wasteland-in-rajasthan-with-community-support%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20reservoirs%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20made%20with%20embankments%20on%20three%20sides%20that%20are%20situated%20at%20the%20end%20of%20diversion%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20diversion%20channels%20known%20as%20pynes%20are%20artificial%20rivulets%20that%20are%20extended%20from%20rivers%20to%20collect%20water%20and%20channel%20it%20to%20the%20Ahars%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months.%20In%20a%20state%20that%20is%20largely%20known%20for%20its%20agricultural%20contribution%2C%20especially%20paddy%20cultivation%2C%20this%20technique%20of%20using%20Ahar%20Pynes%20is%20exceptionally%20useful%20in%20low-rainfall%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EApatani%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-280154%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apatani%20is%20used%20in%20the%20rural%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20for%20wet%20rice%20cultivation%20and%20fish%20farming.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1-1648034024-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-280154%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EApatani%20is%20used%20in%20the%20rural%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20for%20wet%20rice%3C%2Fem%3E%20c%3Cem%3Eultivation%20and%20fish%20farming.%20Picture%20Credits%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcpreecenvis.nic.in%2FDatabase%2FApataniFarmingSystem_3788.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEIACP%20Programme%20Centre%2C%20Resource%20Partner%20on%20Ecological%20Heritage%20and%20Sacred%20Sites%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPractised%20by%20the%20Apatani%20tribes%20of%20Ziro%2C%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20Apatani%20system%20is%20used%20to%20harvest%20both%20ground%20and%20surface%20water%20for%20irrigation.%20In%20this%20system%2C%20valleys%20are%20cut%20into%20terraced%20plots%20separated%20by%200.6%20meters%20high%20earthen%20dams%20that%20are%20supported%20by%20bamboo%20frames.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20plots%20have%20an%20inlet%20and%20outlet%20on%20the%20opposite%20sides.%20Deeper%20channels%20are%20also%20created%20that%20connect%20the%20inlet%20point%20to%20the%20outlet%20point%2C%20so%20that%20the%20terraced%20plots%20can%20be%20flooded%20or%20drained%20off%20with%20water%20simply%20by%20opening%20or%20blocking%20these%20inlets%20and%20outlets%2C%20as%20per%20requirement.%20This%20method%20of%20water%20harvesting%20is%20still%20used%20in%20the%20rural%20parts%20of%20the%20state%2C%20especially%20in%20wet%20rice%20cultivation%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F406762%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-innovative-solutions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efish%20farming.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBaoli%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-280155%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-2-1648034157.jpg%5C%22%20